@node past "What I have missed by being in caves?"

	Past | @{" Present " link present} | @{" Future " link future}

	History: (* = public release)

300995	0.01	Printed values to window.
011095	0.02	Coded equalizers.
	0.03	No more uses AmigaE drawing functions.
021295	0.04	Gained more speed by writing directly to bitplanes by using
		BltBitMapRastPort() routine. Should be system friendly.
031295	0.05	Rewrote hole bar routine, now looks much better. Optimized.
		Uses main and sample volume to adjust bars.
081295*	0.06	Code optimizations.
101295	0.06kp	Bug fixes and a pre-release to KP.
241295*	0.07	No more crash if no module loaded.
		Cache optimized draw routine.
		Cache optimized average count routine.
291295	0.08	Added more safety to HiPPort handling. Code optimized.
		Cache optimized overflow check routine.
		Cache optimized bar subtraction routine.
		Some adding and subtraction bugs fixed.
240296*	1.0	SPIScope seems to be quite stable, so a major release.
		Code optimized.
		Done Amigaguide documents.
011296*	1.2	Changed to assembly code because of SPi-Scope was 90%
		assembly code anyway. Some optimizations added.
		Bugs fixed. SPi-Scope was drawing 2nd and 4th chnl wrong.
		Cosmetic changes.
		Windowposition can be given from commandline. (only 4 KS36+)
		Sensi value can be given from commandline. (only 4 KS36+)
310397*	1.21	Now should draw left and right PT stereochannels correct.
260597*	1.22	Maintinance release. Cleaned code.
@endnode

@node present "Apocalypse Now!"

	@{" Past " link past} | Present | @{" Future " link future}

110897	1.29	Total rewrite of code. Smaller, faster and more attractive!
		Now looks like I have always wanted it to look.
		Average routine removed by clever coding.
		Now only reads 4 channel bar infos against old 4+2.
		New HippoPlayer functions included.
		PS3M scope is not ready yet.
@endnode

@node future "To boldly go where no man has ever gone.."

	@{" Past " link past} | @{" Present " link present} | Future

xxxx97	1.3	Added PS3M scope.
		020+ optimized version.

	Who  knows?  Send @{" me " link credits} suggestions, comments, bug reports and
	other stuff.

@endnode

@node techinfo "dc.l $SPiScope ... ?!?"

	Coded with pure Assembler using SNMA 2.73.

	SPi-Scope can be started from WB.

	SPi-Scope runs at priority -30 like KP`s scopes.

	Tested with:

	A1200/2M Chip/210M HD/2 Floppys
	A1200/030/50Mhz CPU/MMU/2M Chip/8M Fast/210M HD/2 Floppys
	A1200/030/50Mhz CPU/50Mhz FPU/MMU/2M Chip/4M Fast/810M HD/2 Floppys
	(note: above 030`s were tested on "phase 5 Blizzard III & IV cards")

	Kickstart 3.0 and Kickstart 3.1.
	Mungwall and Enforcer. (and Executive)
@endnode

@node usage "How to control this beast?"

USAGE:	SPiScope [X=WindowXPos] [Y=WindowYPos] [S=Sensi]

	WindowXPos and WindowYPos is position where SPiScope's window
	will open.

	SENSI means how many times a sample is read. (in a channel)
	(Example: Sensi 10, read 10 sample bytes before proceeding to
	next channel)

NOTE!:	These commandline arguments only work with KS36+. If you have
	a older KS, then you should upgrade.
@endnode

